# Patterns to ignore when building Helm chart packages.
#
# Reference docs that live in the chart root (and never inside
# templates/) so the Helm provider does not try to parse them as
# resources.
vendored-cni-NOTES.md

# Terragrunt drops a `.terragrunt-source-manifest` file in every copied
# subdirectory when the consumer Terragrunt unit pulls this module via
# its `terraform { source = "..." }` block. .helmignore is NOT honored
# by the helm Terraform provider (it loads the chart from the source
# path directly, bypassing `helm package`), so a Terragrunt-side hook
# is still required to actually remove these. The pattern here documents
# intent; the operational removal happens in
# `vpn2/deploy/garuda/terragrunt.hcl` (before_hook
# strip_terragrunt_manifests_from_charts).
.terragrunt-source-manifest
